snippet.textDisplay: Hi Shane and Ryan! My name is Addie Pietrowski and I absolutely LOVE your shows. Thank you so much for keeping Unsolved going during this terrible time. I know you guys haven't had the paranormal section of Unsolved going recently, but I'd like to bring to your attention the Eloise Sanitarium in Westland Michigan. This place really confuses me and I'd like to know exactly what happened to my Great Aunt Sophie. She was put in Eloise when she was in a car crash. She had brain damage, but while her stay at Eloise, family members say that she was acting even weirder and lost then she did at home. When and if you ever get time, I'd like you to please check out the Eloise Sanitarium if you haven't already. Again, a big fan of the show and thank you from Mackinaw City Michigan. :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey guys, next true crime you should look into the Richard Oland case. It is based here in Canada (New Brunswick) and was an extremely high profile case with a lot of questionable evidence and a trial that lasted quite a few years. The case is still unsolved but there was one main suspect (I won't spoil anything) and it's a really weird and interesting case. If you are bored during quarantine The Canadian True Crime podcast on spotify has a three part series explaining the whole thing. Here's the link; I really hope you guys take a listen and enjoy it!


https://open.spotify.com/episode/5X0xB4wTqbKVJqfHFJWG6G?si=Ui7LYU9ySr-iABsqY65b5g


P.S.
will you ever visit Canada after this quarantine is up, are you interested in coming here, where would you like to go if you did travel to Canada (I'm from Nova Scotia so you guys should probably come here one day lol)
